QUICKSTART - Maximus BBS
========================

This guide gets you running a Maximus BBS in minutes.

OPTION A: Using Pre-built Releases (Recommended)
-------------------------------------------------

1. Download the latest release for your platform from:
   https://github.com/LimpingNinja/maximus/releases

2. Extract and enter the directory:

   $ tar -xzvf maximus-VERSION-PLATFORM.tar.gz
   $ cd maximus-VERSION-PLATFORM

3. Run the install script to configure your BBS:

   $ bin/install.sh

   Follow the prompts to set your BBS name and sysop name.
   The script automatically compiles all configuration files.

4. Create your sysop account by logging in locally:

   $ bin/runbbs.sh -c

   Enter your sysop name, create a password, and exit with G (Goodbye).

5. Start accepting callers with MAXTEL:

   $ bin/maxtel -p 2323 -n 4

   Connect with: telnet localhost 2323


OPTION B: Building from Source
------------------------------

1. Clone or download the source:

   $ git clone https://github.com/LimpingNinja/maximus.git
   $ cd maximus

2. Build using the platform script:

   macOS:  $ ./scripts/build-macos.sh
   Linux:  $ ./scripts/build-linux.sh

3. The built system is in build/. Run install.sh to configure:

   $ cd build
   $ bin/install.sh

4. Create your sysop account and start MAXTEL as above.


RUNNING YOUR BBS
----------------

Interactive mode (with ncurses dashboard):
   $ bin/maxtel -p 2323 -n 4

Headless mode (no UI, for scripts/supervisors):
   $ bin/maxtel -p 2323 -n 4 -H

Daemon mode (runs in background):
   $ bin/maxtel -p 2323 -n 4 -D

Local console mode (direct sysop access):
   $ bin/runbbs.sh -c


CONFIGURATION
-------------

After running install.sh, you can further customize:

- etc/max.ctl      - Main BBS configuration
- etc/menus.ctl    - Menu definitions
- etc/msgarea.ctl  - Message area definitions
- etc/filearea.ctl - File area definitions

After editing .ctl files, recompile with:
   $ bin/recompile.sh


